  to be used by MSBuild. See the PowerShell script Build.ps1.

  Common command line options for MSBuild:

    /nologo /maxcpucount

  Target environment command line options:
  
    /property:Configuration=Release
    /property:Configuration=Debug
    /property:Platform=Win32
    /property:Platform=x64

  Target selection command line options  

    /target:BuildAll .......... Build everything.
    /target:BuildDLL .......... Build TSDuck DLL only.
    /target:BuildTests ........ Build unitary test programs and their dependencies.
    /target:BuildPlugins ...... Build tsp plugins and their dependencies.
    /target:BuildCommands ..... Build command line tools and their dependencies.
    /target:BuildInstaller .... Build what is needed in a TSDuck installer.

